  "text": "## LLVM Optimization Pass Pipeline Lifecycle\n\n### 1. PassBuilder Class Definition\n**File:** `llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h` (lines 108-280)\n\nThe `PassBuilder` class is the primary interface for constructing LLVM optimization pass pipelines. Key method:\n- **`buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline(OptimizationLevel Level, ThinOrFullLTOPhase Phase)`** (lines 258-260): Builds the default per-module optimization pipeline that corresponds to typical -O[123] optimization levels.\n\nThis class also provides:\n- `buildModuleSimplificationPipeline()` - Core module canonicalization and simplification\n- `buildModuleOptimizationPipeline()` - Module-level optimizations focusing on execution speed\n- `buildFunctionSimplificationPipeline()` - Per-function canonicalization and simplification\n\n### 2. PassManager Template Class\n**File:** `llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h` (lines 159-226)\n\nThe `PassManager` template class is the core pass execution engine:\n```cpp\ntemplate <typename IRUnitT,\n          typename AnalysisManagerT = AnalysisManager<IRUnitT>,\n          typename... ExtraArgTs>\nclass PassManager : public PassInfoMixin<...>\n```\n\nKey components:\n- **`run(IRUnitT &IR, AnalysisManagerT &AM, ExtraArgTs... ExtraArgs)`** (line 190-191): Executes all passes in sequence over the given IR unit\n- **`addPass(PassT &&Pass)`** (lines 193-202): Adds a pass to the manager using concept-based polymorphism\n- **Passes vector** (line 225): Stores passes as unique_ptr to PassConceptT interface for type erasure\n\nTypedefs provide convenience types:\n- `ModulePassManager = PassManager<Module>` (line 238)\n- `FunctionPassManager = PassManager<Function>` (line 247)\n\n### 3. PassBuilderPipelines Implementation\n**File:** `llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp` (lines 1715-1761)\n\nThe `buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline` implementation assembles the complete pipeline:\n```cpp\nModulePassManager\nPassBuilder::buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline(OptimizationLevel Level,\n                                           ThinOrFullLTOPhase Phase)\n```\n\nPipeline assembly order (lines 1730-1760):\n1. MemProf cleanup (if not in LTO mode)\n2. Annotation metadata conversion\n3. Force function attributes\n4. Module simplification pipeline via `buildModuleSimplificationPipeline()`\n5. Module optimization pipeline via `buildModuleOptimizationPipeline()`\n6. Pseudo-probe updates (for profiling)\n7. Annotation remarks\n8. LTO pre-link passes (if applicable)\n\n### 4. Pass Registration via PassRegistry.def\n**File:** `llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def` (lines 1-200+)\n\nThis file is the centralized registry of all standard passes. It is #include'd multiple times in `PassBuilder.cpp` with different macro definitions (MODULE_PASS, FUNCTION_PASS, CGSCC_PASS, LOOP_PASS, MODULE_ANALYSIS, FUNCTION_ANALYSIS, etc.).\n\nExample entries from the registry:\n- **Module Passes** (lines 51-190): ForceFunctionAttrs, DeadArgumentElimination, GlobalOpt, Inlining, etc.\n- **Function Passes**: InstCombine, SimplifyCFG, SROA, etc. (not shown in sample, but follow same pattern)\n- **Analyses**: CallGraph, LazyCallGraph, ProfileSummary, etc.\n\nThe DeadStoreElimination pass is registered as a FUNCTION_PASS in this file.\n\n### 5. Concrete Example: DeadStoreElimination\n**Header File:** `llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Scalar/DeadStoreElimination.h`\n**Implementation:** `llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/DeadStoreElimination.cpp` (lines 1-50)\n\nThe `DeadStoreElimination` pass (DSE) is a concrete example of an optimization pass that:\n- Implements the pass logic using MemorySSA (Memory Static Single Assignment form)\n- Uses the pattern: Walk from a MemoryDef upward to find clobbering MemoryDefs, verify no intervening reads, then eliminate dead stores\n- Includes headers for MemorySSA, PostDominators, LoopInfo, and AliasAnalysis\n- Is registered in PassRegistry.def as a FUNCTION_PASS\n- Can be included and used in pass pipelines like buildModuleOptimizationPipeline\n\n## Pipeline Execution Chain\n\n1. **Pipeline Construction**: PassBuilder::buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline() creates a ModulePassManager\n2. **Component Assembly**: Adds module simplification and optimization pipelines via function calls\n3. **Pass Registration**: Each pass is created via constructors specified in PassRegistry.def\n4. **Execution**: PassManager::run() iterates through Passes vector and executes each pass\n5. **Analysis Management**: Each pass receives AnalysisManager for requesting required analyses\n6. **Invalidation**: PreservedAnalyses from each pass triggers analysis invalidation\n\nThis architecture enables: modular pipeline construction, late binding of pass implementations, flexible pass composition, and efficient analysis caching and invalidation."
